Dear Google Recruiter:

 I would like to request your consideration for a position in the 2023 Student Training in Engineering Program.

 My goal is to become a developer who has a good influence on people, thus I was greatly excited by Google's Student Training in Engineering Program. I applied for the position to inspire creativity through experience at the world's best company and contribute to Google and the world.

 I am majoring in computer science and engineering at Pohang University of Science and Technology, and completed essential courses such as object-oriented programming, computer architecture, operating system, and algorithms, laying the foundation as a developer. Currently, I am serving military service as a software engineer at the Republic of Korea Army Headquarters.

 I have developed my competencies through the following experiences:
 - I maintained a legacy system written over 10 years ago. I put a lot of technical consideration to improve the scalability and maintainability of the program to refactor the legacy system into a clean code.
 - I proposed a project to integrate multiple kickboard services into a single application to resolve the inconvenience of service users. My team realized this proposal into an integrated kickboard service by signing MOUs with 2 companies.

 Please find my resume or portfolio in the attachment. If you need any more details, please do let me know. I would appreciate the opportunity to discuss my qualification more fully in an interview. Thank you for your consideration.

